167
00:12:12,272 --> 00:12:14,558
Kiss were four glam rock fans

168
00:12:14,658 --> 00:12:16,851
who hit upon the idea
of using makeup

169
00:12:16,951 --> 00:12:20,332
to transform themselves into
larger-than-life rock stars.

170
00:12:20,874 --> 00:12:24,134
The plan was to create an illusion.

171
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:29,611
Because if you can get people
to believe what they're seeing

172
00:12:29,711 --> 00:12:33,829
is more than what it is,
it becomes more than it is.

173
00:12:33,929 --> 00:12:41,054
# I wanna rock and roll all nite
and party every day

174
00:12:42,994 --> 00:12:45,141
Kiss were hated by
music critics,

175
00:12:45,241 --> 00:12:47,328
but built up a fan base of millions,

176
00:12:47,428 --> 00:12:51,449
because their shows could successfully
entertain tens of thousands of people.

177
00:12:51,939 --> 00:12:54,323
It's not spontaneous.
Everything is scripted.

178
00:12:54,423 --> 00:12:57,581
The focus is not necessarily
on the music.

179
00:12:57,681 --> 00:13:00,178
The frontman basically
is barely playing.

180
00:13:00,278 --> 00:13:03,450
He misses more notes than he hits.

181
00:13:03,530 --> 00:13:05,748
The emphasis is on the spectacle.

182
00:13:06,818 --> 00:13:10,796
I could care less whether
'New Musical Express'

183
00:13:10,896 --> 00:13:14,812
or some other music magazine
believes that what we do is valid.

184
00:13:14,912 --> 00:13:19,387
A billion dollars later,
they can kiss my ass, baby!

185
00:13:22,050 --> 00:13:23,679
The band was deliberately marketed

186
