At their peak, Kiss earned $50 million
a year from merchandise alone.

196
00:13:57,089 --> 00:13:59,061
Their products could be found
everywhere.

197
00:13:59,261 --> 00:14:02,402
Even in the dressing room of the man
who would eventually deliver

198
00:14:02,502 --> 00:14:05,872
stadium rock from this glam
and platform heel phase,

199
00:14:05,972 --> 00:14:07,558
Bruce Springsteen.

200
00:14:10,831 --> 00:14:14,978
Bruce Springsteen was one
of the first people viewed as

201
00:14:15,078 --> 00:14:18,411
being necessary to save
rock 'n roll.

202
00:14:18,511 --> 00:14:21,008
He was a good looking guy,
writing great songs,

203
00:14:21,108 --> 00:14:25,785
who seemed, more than anything else,
relentlessly sincere.

204
00:14:26,729 --> 00:14:29,941
He is the 70s rock Dylan.

